cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.SY 

The paper deals with video streaming algorithms, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI) aspects. It also involves information theory (cs.IT) as the algorithms aim to maximize video streaming quality subject to queue stability. The use of 4K UHD video traces suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the performance improvements with the stochastic video streaming algorithms suggest control systems (cs.SY) as another possible sub-category.
